You have successfully completed all the necessary setup tasks, and Service Cloud Voice is now operational. While it is not mandatory, you have the option to customize Service Cloud Voice further, unlocking advanced capabilities that can significantly enhance the overall experience for your customers, agents, and supervisors.

Customization Options by Telephony Model
Congratulations, you set up the basic version of Service Cloud Voice and configured the contact center. To enable more advanced features, complete these optional customizations. The list of customizations varies based on your telephony model.
 
Customize Your Contact Center
Grant more agents and supervisors access to voice call records and call recordings. Configure Amazon Connect instance to seamlessly integrate with Service Cloud Voice. Add queues and define dynamic routing rules with Omni-Channel flows.

Customize the Agent Experience
Give support agents the information they need to help customers on the phone.

Customize the Supervisor Experience
Enhance how supervisors interact with agents, customers, and your contact center by customizing Omni Supervisor.

Automate Your Contact Center with Artificial Intelligence
Optimize contact center operations using AI. Gauge sentiment of call conversations. Trigger actions based on signals and keywords detected during a conversation. Turn on AI-generated call summaries for efficient analysis.

Integrate Service Cloud Voice with Sales Engagement
Maximize sales reps' productivity by combining Service Cloud Voice with Sales Engagement.

Preparing Your Network for Service Cloud Voice
Minimize connectivity problems by preparing your network and agent machines for Service Cloud Voice.
title: Customizing Service Cloud Voice
